We unfortunately had to say good bye to @federico.pietrucci today...
.
Due to his injury...
.
I know all about the feeling when it feels like something is taken away from you. As I myself raptured my achilles tendon in 2017 in the middle of filming a dutch movie. Still remember that as if it was yesterday.
.
Don't think about it to much. It happened and there is nothing you can do about it... The only way is forward..so focuss on your recovery now and come back stronger then ever!
.
I want to wish you @federico.pietrucci  a speedy recovery and lots of luck with all of your dance ventures in the future! Hopefully see you soon friend. It was a pleasure working with you the past months. You're an amazing dancer and human. üí™üèΩüî•. #amici2019

.
.
Danced by @federico.pietrucci
.
This choreo was a little different then how usually choreograph. I like trying out different things. Not only to challenge myself but also to see the capacity of our students and off course to keep surprising you guys, the audience!
.
.
Speaking of the audience! Haha...I want to start of that I love your energy and you enthousiasm. But I have to share one of my biggest pet peeves during a live performance...
.
"CLAPPING OFF BEAT" or "CLAPPING DOUBLE TEMPO".....üòÖüò∂üëÄ.
.
I know for a fact it's not always your fault. Sometimes there is someone that warms up the audience and tells you to clap..and other times its you just being super supportive and hyped up! üòÖüòäüôèüèΩ.
.
The thing is...its very distracting sometimes for me watching and I can imagine also the other judges. We are trying to feel the performance..not only during the dancing but also during  the singing performances... because some songs have a natural build up to it..which brings up an emotion or a vibe with it...and then if it gets abrubted with sudden off beat or double tempo claps...well you knowüòÖ‚ò†....
.
Also the performers on stage they are focussed and out of experience...it sometimes throws you offüòÖ.
.
Anyway! Here is a TIP!üôèüèΩüî•
.
TIP: You don't always have to clap on each count. Like 1-2-4-5-6-7-8. This could work with House,edm,techno etc..Its different with each type of song & Genre.
.
With Most Pop,Hip Hop & R&B songs. We clap on the 2-4-6 & 8 count of the song. Easy way to figure this out. Is to just clap on the SNARE...and not the KICK.
.
And in other occasions...no clapping at all. Haha.
.
Anyway! Try it out and see for yourself! It sounds way more funky and chill. And it goes WITH the vibe of the song like you make love to itüòç. Instead of fighting itü•äü•ã.
.
I hope this helps! Anyway I want to say one more time! We all love your energy and enthousiasm! Much Love to all of you for the support!üôèüèΩüíï‚ù§
.
.

What a very bizarre show we had today! .
Here are some thoughts about today.üëáüèΩüëáüèΩ
(üáÆüáπGuarda la mia storia. Per la traduzione italiana.)
.
I want to start of with saying that it was so much fun to dance with Maria,The professors,all of the students and the dancers.üòçü§©üî•
.
It was a reminder that we don't have to take things so seriously all the time. To also have fun and celebrate dance. For me dancing is something that gives joy and a sense of freedom without any restrictions.. So I really want to encourage everyone reading this to dance more and have fun with it!üòä‚ù§
.
Secondly, I think you've all seen what happened today. I really want you guys to know that I wanted to say so much more in responds to the boy who spoke without respect towards me. Trust me...But I chose as a teacher but most importantly as a grown man to not disrespect him back..but instead to try and understand the reasoning and point of view and be mature about it. Because I always try to remember that knowledge makes people humble while ignorance makes people arrogant.
.
All I want to say for now is that Talent itself means nothing...while experience aquired in humility and hard work means everything. With that being said..There is work to do. The boy needs help and needs to understand how to properly carry himself and how to manage his words when speaking to others. Not just me...Because it would be a shame if his talent gets overshadowed by his immature, ignorant and bad attitude.
.
What are your thoughts about todays show?
.
#amici19 #amici2019 #teacher #choreographer

Sometimes it's not easy to be a judge and teacher in @amiciufficiale ...
.
What are your thoughts!?
.
Situations like today. The moment when things are said and done...it has its consequences. .
When a conflict happends it can lead to trigger an emotional response...a problem within...that touches us.
we then have 2 choices:
.
1: To act and reply right away out of emotionüî•..(sometimes this leads into saying things without thinking)
2: To take a moment to let things sink in and thinküí≠...and then give rational response. (Which gives you time to select your words with more precision and accuracy.)
.
.
I try to always choose #2. It's the hardest one. Specially for people who are very connected with their emotions and very passionate. But it will lead to a longer path of happiness. I try to help my students understand that as well. It's more than just a dancing journey towards your dreams, it's also about all the obstacles on the way to the top.
.
.
üáÆüáπüáÆüáπüáÆüáπ.
A volte non √® facile essere giudice e insegnante ad Amici.

Quali sono I pensieri? 
Situazioni come oggi. Il momento in cui le cose vengono dette e fatte... questo ha le sue conseguenze. .
Quando si verifica un conflitto, la risposta pu√≤ essere emotiva ... un problema interiore ... che ci tocca.
.
A quel punto noi abbiamo due scelte:
.
1: agire e rispondere subito presi dalle emozioni üî• (e a volte questo porta a dire cose senza pensare).
.
2: prendersi un momento per approfondire le cose e pensare üí≠... e poi dare una risposta razionale. (Questo dar√† il tempo di selezionare le parole con pi√π precisione e accuratezza).
.
Io provo sempre a scegliere la #2. √à la pi√π difficile. Specialmente per la gente molto connessa con le proprie emozioni e passionale. Ma porter√† a un percorso pi√π lungo verso la felicit√†. 
Provo a far capire ai miei studenti anche questo. √à pi√π di un semplice viaggio danzante verso il proprio sogno, riguarda anche tutti gli ostacoli che si incontreranno sulla strada verso la vetta.
.
